{
  "texts": [
    "It should be noted that the model is isothermal and formulated as a planar 2D model rather than an axisymmetric one.",
    "Table 3 shows the material parameters of the Giesekus model for PLA material, which are similar to the viscoelastic model parameters of PLA in (Schuller et al., 2024a).",
    "The material parameters of PLA, the feeding rate, and the geometry lead to high Wi numbers, which are known to cause numerical difficulties (Keunings, 1986) and lead to the formation of large vortices.",
    "Continuation techniques are required to achieve convergence at high Wi numbers, where the relaxation time is gradually increased and the mobility factor is decreased.",
    "This procedure raises the computational cost by a factor of 10-20."
  ]
}